RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOLLY DIMPLE gained the early lead racing about the two path, shook off a mild bid from FLIRTATIOUS SMILE in the far turn and held safe in the lane. FLIRTATIOUS SMILE tracked the winner from outside and could not get to that one in the lane. FAST SOPHIA moved three to four wide to gain position going to the far turn but could not threaten in the lane. PRAIRIE FIREBALL was with the early leaders from along the inside and tired. ANGIE'S REVRAC failed to mount a bid. SERENGETI SIX dropped out in the far turn and was eased through the lane, walked off.

MOST AMUSING tracked the winner outside to bid through the far turn into the lane but could not go with that one late. SPEEDY FELLAR followed the pace3 from along the inside, angled outside the leaders into the lane but could not close the gap. RANCHO BARGO saved ground and could not threaten in the drive. LADDIE BOY failed to mount a bid. RUBIGINOUS followed the pace three to four wide and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 63. Allowance Purse 8100. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VIRTUALLY stalked the early leaders four wide to challenge going up the backstretch, continued outside RETRO RITA through the far turn and edged clear in the lane. RAINBOW DASH moved up three wide in the far turn and gained the place late. RETRO RITA contended the pace out from the rail, continued with the winner in the far turn but came up empty late. WUMPMUG weakened along the inside. TROUBLE IN RED was five and six wide through the first turn and failed to threaten. GRAND EXPECTATIONS showed speed but floated out from the inside in the first turn and gave way going to the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Retro Rita
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied off rail, bid, empty late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 6300. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE SEPTEMBER 24, 2022. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRINEE made the pace on a short lead along the inside, continued well into the lane and edged away late. SHEZA SAVAGE was just off the pace along the inside then dropped back in traffic behind the leaders going to the far turn, came again in the lane and rallied clear for the place. BOLD LEGEND broke in the air, followed the pace three and four wide then moved up in the lane but could not threaten the top pair. UNHERDOF was just off the early leaders while three to four wide and weakened in the drive. NEBRASKA RED tracked the winner three wide and weakene3d in the drive. REMARKABLE CHARM failed to mount a bid four wide. STARLIGHT TWIST was always back. BLUEBIRD DAY saved ground and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 81. Starter Allowance Purse 7300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $3,500 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OLD TRAFFORD stalked the dueling leaders three wide, challenged through the far turn to show in front turning for home and moved off under steady handling. HOT ARTIE dueled on the pace outside PARLAY PETE to the far turn then could not go with the winner in the drive. SILVER MAKER saved ground in reach of the pace, continued along the rail and was blocked through midstretch, took back and gaied third late. PARLAY PETE dueled in HOT ARTIE early, continued to late in the far turn and came up empty. RANDOM AFFAIR failed to rally three wide.

ENTRY.NAME: Old Trafford
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3wd, bid far turn, drew away
